    • Constructor Detail

      • DoubleListParam

        public DoubleListParam(java.lang.String name,
                       java.lang.String title,
                       java.lang.String description,
                       java.lang.Double minValue,
                       java.lang.Double maxValue,
                       java.util.List<java.lang.Double> defaultValue,
                       java.lang.Double step)
        minValue, maxValue and step will be applied to each element of input list
        Parameters:
        name - Should be unique among parameters of a pattern
        title - no constraint
        description - no constraint
        minValue - defines minimum of range of selection. Default = Double.MIN_VALUE
        maxValue - defines maximum of range of selection. Default = Double.MAX_VALUE
        defaultValue - predefined array of values
        step - if Double.isInfinite() or Double.isNaN() or null or 0, step will be set to 1.0
        if negative, step will be the opposite value

      • setCurrentValue

        public void setCurrentValue(java.lang.Object newValue)
        Restore to the default value if the list does not contain valid Double
        Specified by:
        setCurrentValue in class PatternParameter
        Parameters:
        newValue - only accept List of Doubles. Else, the current value will be erased. Each element will be round up by step and set to:
        • 0.0 if Double.isInfinite() or Double.isNaN() or null
        • minValue if lower than minValue
        • maxValue if higher than maxValue
